## 📊 YOLOv8 Detection Verification Run

We ran standard YOLOv8 person detection on this image to verify compatibility. The model successfully identified human shapes, cars, and personal items:

```text
Inference Resolution: 640x640
Execution Speed: 261.0ms
Detections:
  - 👥 22 Persons (class 0.0)
  - 🚗 7 Cars (class 2.0)
  - 🏍️ 1 Motorcycle (class 3.0)
  - 🎒 2 Backpacks (class 24.0)
  - ☂️ 1 Umbrella (class 25.0)
  - 👜 1 Handbag (class 26.0)
```

### Verification Bounding Box Script
You can inspect the bounding boxes on the generated image using the following script:
```python
from ultralytics import YOLO
import cv2

model = YOLO('yolov8n.pt')
results = model('benchmark_data/blr_street_cctv_yolo.png')

# Show detections and save annotated output
annotated_img = results[0].plot()
cv2.imwrite('benchmark_results/annotated_blr_street_cctv_yolo.png', annotated_img)
print("Annotated image saved successfully.")
```
